The shape, size and crystallinity of the biogenic TiO2 NPs were determined by TEM [71] (JEM-2100plus, JEOL, Japan), SAED pattern [72], EDX spectrophotometer [73] and XRD [3]. XRD analysis was performed using an X-ray diffractometer with Cu-Kα crystal radiation (λ = 1.54060 Å) and scanning rate of (5°/min−1) and the scanning range of (10°—80°). The Scherrer equation was used to calculate the mean diameter of the NPs from the XRD pattern as follows [74]:3D=0.9λ/βcosθ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
